{"type":"message","id":"7b8e8ce7","parentId":"2db38028","timestamp":"2026-02-17T19:19:17.256Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-02-17 21:19 GMT+2] OPERATION: TOKEN ECONOMY (TWO-TIER REPORTING).\n\n1.  **Reporting Logic (`scripts/run_archivist.py`):**\n    *   Implement dual output: `FULL_` (raw LLM response) and `SUMMARY_` (first 10 lines or specific extraction).\n    *   *Prompt for Summary:* \"Summarize this in <1000 chars. Use emojis. Structure: Pros, Cons, Verdict.\"\n\n2.  **Protocol Update (Section 17):**\n    *   Add Rule: \"Telegram = Summary Only. File Link required.\"\n\n3.  **Generate Summary (Retroactive):**\n    *   Read `docs/FINAL_AUDIT_REPORT.md`.\n    *   Write `docs/SUMMARY_AUDIT.md`:\n        *   ✅ SACS-2026, OODA, SharedMemory.\n        *   ⚠️ Rust Legacy, Manual Scripts, Local UI.\n        *   🏁 READY (Legacy Speed).\n\n4.  **Output:**\n    *   `type docs/SUMMARY_AUDIT.md` (via `exec_guard`)."}],"timestamp":1771355957254}}
